==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Greek]] '''[[δυστοπία]]''' (''dystopia'') "bad place, unlucky place", from [[Ancient Greek]] prefix '''[[δυσ-]]''' (''dys-'') "un-, mis-", with notion of "hard, bad, unlucky", etc. + '''[[τόπος]]''' (''topos'') "place, region", metaph. "occasion, opportunity".

===Noun===
'''dystopia'''
# A vision of a future that is a [[corrupt]]ed (usually beyond recognition) [[utopian]] society
# State in which the condition of life is extremely bad as from deprivation or oppression or terror

